== Configuration ==
Usually a display manager is started automatically on boot.

=== OpenRC ===
If you use [[OpenRC]] init system (default), the XDM init script handles the starting of the various display managers. You need to configure your default display manager, e.g. for KDM:
{{File|/etc/conf.d/xdm||<pre>
DISPLAYMANAGER="kdm"
</pre>}}

To start KDM on boot, add xdm to your default runlevel:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add xdm default}}

To start KDM now:
{{RootCmd|/etc/init.d/xdm start}}

=== systemd ===
If you use [[systemd]] init system, first you have to get the {{Path|.service}} file yourself. Some are in the [http://git.overlays.gentoo.org/gitweb/?p=user/systemd.git;a=tree;f=sys-apps/systemd-units/files/services-desktop systemd] [[overlay]]. Pick one and move it to {{Path|/etc/systemd/system}} or install sys-apps/systemd-units from the overlay.

To start e.g. KDM on boot, enable the service:
{{RootCmd|systemctl enable kdm.service}}

To start KDM now:
{{RootCmd|systemctl start kdm.service}}

